---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About the SwiftUI Architecture community resource library."
>
  <section class="page-hero compact">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span></span> About the project</span>
      <h1>A useful map of the SwiftUI architecture community.</h1>
      <p>
        SwiftUI Architecture is a curated knowledge base created by Mohammad
        Azam. It links to useful work published by Apple, independent developers,
        authors, educators, and open-source maintainers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
      <p>
        Valuable SwiftUI architecture material is spread across personal blogs,
        videos, conference sessions, books, and GitHub repositories. This site
        organizes those resources around practical topics instead of presenting
        an endless chronological feed.
      </p>

      <h2>Editorial approach</h2>
      <p>
        Resources are selected for clarity, practical usefulness, and relevance
        to production SwiftUI development. The site links to the original
        publisher and may include a short summary explaining why the resource is
        useful.
      </p>

      <h2>Community first</h2>
      <p>
        The library includes Mohammad Azam’s work alongside resources from the
        broader Swift community. Inclusion does not imply endorsement of every
        architectural decision. Different approaches can be valuable when their
        tradeoffs are explained clearly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
